{"title_page": "Cueva de los Pincheira", "text_new": "'''Cueva del los Pincheira''' is a shallow cave located about 65 km southeast of [[Chill\u00e1n]], in [[\u00d1uble Region]], [[Central Chile]]. The cave is famous for being a hideout of the [[Pincheira brothers]], a [[Royalist (Spanish American independence)|royalist]] [[banditry in Chile|outlaw gang]]. During high season there are reeanactments in the cave.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/chile/attractions/cueva-de-los-pincheira/a/poi-sig/1507625/363257|title=Cueva de los Pincheira|date=|access-date=2020-04-20|website=[[Lonely Planet]]}}</ref>\n\nThe cave lies in the footwills of the Andes near [[Laguna Huemul]].<ref name=Arna2011/> In the 1820s the cave was one of the Pincheira brothers main encampments together with other locations also close to Chill\u00e1n. Up to thousand people are reported to have gathered at the site during the heydays of the Pincheira brothers.<ref name=Arna2011>Arnaboldi, Teresa (2011). [http://hacerfamilia.cl/2011/10/la-reivindicacion-de-los-pincheiras/ \"La reivindicaci\u00f3n de los Pincheira\"]. Revista ''Hacer Familia'', n.\u00ba&nbsp;186. October 13, 2011. Retrieved January 31, 2014.</ref>\n\nLoca lore says that a white mule appears during the night in the small waterfall of the cave.<ref name=Sonia2015>{{Cite book|title=Mitos de Chile: Enciclopedia de seres, apariciones y encantos|last=Montecino Aguirre|first=Sonia|publisher=[[Catalonia (publisher)|Catalonia]]|year=2015|isbn=978-956-324-375-8|page=197|language=Spanish}}</ref> Allegedly this mule shows the route to the hidden treaures of the Pincheira brothers.<ref name=Sonia2015/> It is also said that just before the morning a cart han be hear near the cave, additionally there are sayings that the cries of women have been heard together the cart.<ref name=Sonia2015/> The sayings explain these are the cries of the women kept captive by the outlaws.<ref name=Sonia2015/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Caves of Chile|Pincheira]]\n[[Category:Landforms of \u00d1uble Region]]\n[[Category:Chilean legends]]\n[[Category:Caves used for hiding]]\n[[Category:Rock shelters]]\n", "text_old": "'''Cueva del los Pincheira''' is a shallow cave located east of [[Chill\u00e1n]], in [[\u00d1uble Region]], [[Central Chile]]. The cave is famous for being a hideout of the [[Pincheira brothers]], a [[Royalist (Spanish American independence)|royalist]] [[banditry in Chile|outlaw gang]]. During high season there are reeanactments in the cave.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/chile/attractions/cueva-de-los-pincheira/a/poi-sig/1507625/363257|title=Cueva de los Pincheira|date=|access-date=2020-04-20|website=[[Lonely Planet]]}}</ref>\n\nThe cave lies in the footwills of the Andes near [[Laguna Huemul]].<ref name=Arna2011/> In the 1820s the cave was one of the Pincheira brothers main encampments together with other locations also close to Chill\u00e1n. Up to thousand people are reported to have gathered at the site during the heydays of the Pincheira brothers.<ref name=Arna2011>Arnaboldi, Teresa (2011). [http://hacerfamilia.cl/2011/10/la-reivindicacion-de-los-pincheiras/ \"La reivindicaci\u00f3n de los Pincheira\"]. Revista ''Hacer Familia'', n.\u00ba&nbsp;186. October 13, 2011. Retrieved January 31, 2014.</ref>\n\nLoca lore says that a white mule appears during the night in the small waterfall of the cave.<ref name=Sonia2015>{{Cite book|title=Mitos de Chile: Enciclopedia de seres, apariciones y encantos|last=Montecino Aguirre|first=Sonia|publisher=[[Catalonia (publisher)|Catalonia]]|year=2015|isbn=978-956-324-375-8|page=197|language=Spanish}}</ref> Allegedly this mule shows the route to the hidden treaures of the Pincheira brothers.<ref name=Sonia2015/> It is also said that just before the morning a cart han be hear near the cave, additionally there are sayings that the cries of women have been heard together the cart.<ref name=Sonia2015/> The sayings explain these are the cries of the women kept captive by the outlaws.<ref name=Sonia2015/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Caves of Chile|Pincheira]]\n[[Category:Landforms of \u00d1uble Region]]\n[[Category:Chilean legends]]\n[[Category:Caves used for hiding]]\n[[Category:Rock shelters]]\n", "name_user": "Sietecolores", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cueva_de_los_Pincheira"}
{"title_page": "Unreal Championship", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{refimprove|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Unreal Championship\n| image = Unrealchampionshipcover.jpg\n| developer = [[Epic Games]]<br />[[Digital Extremes]]\n| publisher = [[Infogrames]]{{efn|Released under the [[Atari]] brand name}}\n| director = \n| producer = \n| designer = [[Cliff Bleszinski]]\n| programmer = [[Steve Polge]]\n| artist = \n| writer = \n| composer = Starsky Partridge\n| series = ''[[Unreal (video game series)|Unreal]]''\n| engine = [[Unreal Engine#Unreal Engine 2|Unreal Engine 2.0]]\n| platforms = [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]]\n| released = {{vgrelease|NA|November 12, 2002<ref name=\"IGNuc\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/games/unreal-championship/xbox-16292 |title=Unreal Championship |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |accessdate=2018-03-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308191837/http://www.ign.com/games/unreal-championship/xbox-16292 |archivedate=2016-03-08 |url-status=dead}}</ref>|EU|November 29, 2002}}\n| genre = [[First-person shooter]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Unreal Championship''''' is a [[first-person shooter]] [[video game]] developed by [[Epic Games]] and [[Digital Extremes]], published by [[Infogrames]], and released for the [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/unreal-championship/|title=Unreal Championship - GameSpot|accessdate=August 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox/unreal-championship|title=Unreal Championship - Metacritic|accessdate=August 30, 2014}}</ref> ''Unreal Championship'' is a console version game of the PC-based ''[[Unreal Tournament 2003]]'', developed to take advantage of [[Xbox Live]], [[Microsoft]]'s online gaming service. In 2003 ''Unreal Championship'' was added to Microsoft's \"Platinum Hits\" line of Xbox games. It was followed in 2005 by ''[[Unreal Championship 2: The Liandri Conflict]]'' also for Xbox.\n\n==Gameplay==\n*'''[[Deathmatch]]'''\n*'''[[Team deathmatch]]'''\n*'''[[Capture the flag]]'''\n*'''Double Domination''' &ndash; In Double Domination both teams must control two points on the map for ten seconds in order to score. A point can be taken by walking into its symbol, A or B. NPCs can be ordered to go to a certain point.\n*'''Survival''' &mdash; 1 vs 1 deathmatch with more players than usual. As each round ends, the losing player is made to join a queue of spectators while the winner remains in the game until killed. The winner is the first player to reach a predetermined score.\n*'''Bombing Run''' &ndash; ''Unreal''-style football where the player's team must score by placing the ball in the enemy force's goal. The bombing gun regenerates health as the offensive player moves, giving him additional lifespan to reach the enemy goal. Once the enemy goal is reached, the offensive player can run into it to score seven points for their team. Shooting the bomb into the enemy goal earns three points.\n\n== Reception ==\n\nThe game received \"generally favorable\" reviews, according to video game [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"metacritic review\"/>\n\n{{Video game reviews\n| title      = Reception\n| subtitle   = \n<!--Formatting-->\n| state      = <!--plain/collapsible-->\n| align      = <!--left/right/none/inherit-->\n<!-- Aggregators -->\n| GR         = 83%<ref name=\"gamerankings review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/xbox/516518-unreal-championship/index.html|title=Unreal Championship Review|work=[[GameRankings]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=October 9, 2014}}</ref>\n| MC         = 83/100<ref name=\"metacritic review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox/unreal-championship|title=Unreal Championship Review|work=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=October 9, 2014}}</ref>\n<!-- Reviewers -->\n| GameRev    = {{Rating|4