} ([[Riyadh]])\n* {{LTU}} (London)\n* {{DPRK}} ([[Kuwait City]])\n* {{MEX}} ([[Riyadh]])<ref>http://www.sre.gob.mx/index.php/embajadas/arabia-saudita</ref>\n* {{NZL}} ([[Riyadh]])\n* {{PAR}} ([[Beirut]])\n* {{POL}} ([[Riyadh]])\n* {{SIN}} ([[Abu Dhabi]])\n* {{VIE}} ([[Kuwait City]])\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Foreign relations of Oman]]\n* [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Oman)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071214212501/http://mofa.gov.om/mofa/ Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Oman]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080505064553/http://www.mofa.gov.om/mofanew/omaniforeginmission.asp Diplomatic list]\n\n{{Asia topic|List of diplomatic missions in}}\n\n[[Category:Foreign relations of Oman]]\n[[Category:Oman diplomacy-related lists|Diplomatic missions]]\n[[Category:Lists of diplomatic missions by receiving country|Oman]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Diplomatic missions in Oman.png|thumb|right|350px|Map of diplomatic missions in Oman]]\nThis is a '''list of diplomatic missions in [[Oman]]'''. There are currently 54 embassies in [[Muscat, Oman|Muscat]] and many countries maintain consulates in other Omani cities (not including honorary consulates).\n\n== Embassies in [[Muscat, Oman|Muscat]] ==\n{| \n|\n*{{Flag|Afghanistan}}\n*{{Flag|Algeria}}\n*{{Flag|Bahrain}}\n*{{Flag|Bangladesh}}\n*{{Flag|Brazil}}\n*{{Flag|Brunei}}\n*{{Flag|China}}\n*{{Flag|Cyprus}}\n*{{Flag|Egypt}} \n*{{Flag|Ethiopia}}\n*{{Flag|France}}\n*{{Flag|Germany}} \n*{{Flag|Hungary}}\n*{{Flag|India}}\n*{{Flag|Indonesia}}\n*{{Flag|Iran}}\n*{{Flag|Iraq}}\n*{{Flag|Italy}}\n*{{Flag|Japan}} \n*{{Flag|Jordan}}\n*{{Flag|Kazakhstan}}\n*{{Flag|Kenya}}\n*{{Flag|Kuwait}}\n*{{Flag|Lebanon}}\n*{{Flag|Libya}}\n*{{Flag|Malaysia}}\n*{{Flag|Mauritania}}\n|valign=top|\n*{{Flag|Morocco}}\n*{{Flag|Nepal}}\n*{{Flag|Netherlands}} \n*{{Flag|Pakistan}}\n*{{Flag|Palestine}}\n*{{Flag|Philippines}} \n*{{Flag|Qatar